# Flint — Core Architecture

Flint is a real-time AI co-pilot desktop app built with Tauri 2.x. It listens to live conversations (interviews etc.), transcribes locally, and surfaces parallel AI responses — invisible to the other party. All real-time processing runs locally. Cloud is only for auth and post-session persistence.

## Tech Stack — Do Not Deviate

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Desktop framework | Tauri 2.x |
| Backend language | Rust (stable, 2021 edition) |
| Async runtime | tokio (multi-thread) |
| Frontend language | TypeScript (strict mode) |
| Frontend framework | React 18 |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS |
| Cloud backend | Supabase (PostgreSQL 15, GoTrue, Storage) |
| Local vector store | sqlite-vec |
| Local DB | SQLite via rusqlite |
| Embedding model | bge-small-en-v1.5 via fastembed-rs |
| Transcription | whisper-rs (Whisper.cpp bindings) |
| Audio capture | cpal |
| Noise suppression | rnnoise-rs |
| VAD | webrtc-vad |
| State (React) | Zustand (UI state only — never session state) |
| Testing (Rust) | cargo test |
| Testing (TS) | Vitest |
| Build/CI | GitHub Actions |

